cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on embedding imputation, which is a common problem in the field of computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel approach that involves using a knowledge graph, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on various tasks, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
